# @ upper()
# The upper() method is used to convert a string to uppercase.
# The upper() method returns a new string with all the characters in uppercase.
# The upper() method does not modify the original string.
# The upper() method is case-sensitive.
# The upper() method does not take any arguments.

str="kingslayer"
print(str.upper()) #Output: KINGSLAYER

# @ lower()
# The lower() method is used to convert a string to lowercase.
# The lower() method returns a new string with all the characters in lowercase.
# The lower() method does not modify the original string.
# The lower() method is case-sensitive.
# The lower() method does not take any arguments.

abc="MOOnnIGHT"
print(abc.lower()) #Output: moonnight

# @ rstrip()
# The rstrip() method is used to remove trailing (Those which occur after a string) whitespace from a string.
# The rstrip() method returns a new string with all the trailing whitespace removed.   
# The rstrip() method does not modify the original string.
# The rstrip() method takes an optional argument that specifies the characters to be removed.
# The rstrip() method is case-sensitive.
# The rstrip() method does not take any arguments.

efg="!!!!!Hello world!!!!!!!"

print(efg.rstrip("!"))
#Output: !!!!!Hello world, the last exclamatory marks have been removed after world


